we make an empty array(stack following lifo) named 'memory' 
1st preference : take right turn 
	after aligned to right , we record theta1 . 
		case1: passage found and bot's orientation is theta2 and theta2-theta1 <=180 degree, store 1 in the array as the path taken was the shortest path. 
		case2: passage found and bot's orientation is theta2 and theta2-theta1 >180 degree, store -1 in the array as the path taken was not the shortest path. 
		case3: it hits a wall. bot turns 180 degree and flips right side hug i.e. if it was 1 so flip to -1 and vice versa.

then while coming out the bot sees the passage in the outer wall , and if there is a passage , it dives in .
after dive cross state is completed then comes the main part , which way does the bot turn to ...
	we access the elements of the array that we made while coming into the maze , and multiply it to the ((math.pi - 0.2) / 2.0) * self.right_side_hug, this leads to either a left turn or a right turn 
	case1: if the element was -1 , this will result in left turn 
	case2: if the element was 1 , this will result in right turn
	
	
